'''Kathryn Schotthoefer''' is an American film and television executive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/digital-creative-agency-heavenspot-adds-598882|title=Digital Creative Agency Heavenspot Adds to Team (Exclusive)|author=Philiana Ng|date=5 August 2013|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> She founded Original Media Ventures, a studio focused on developing film and TV projects from underrepresented creative voices in 2017 and launched REPRESENT, a community to offer support, education, and opportunities for storytellers, in 2018. She previously worked for entertainment companies including [[Twentieth Century Fox]], [[New Line Cinema]], [[Warner Bros.]], and was the former president of [[M&C Saatchi]] company, Heavenspot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mcsaatchi-la.com/kathryn-schotthoefer-named-president-of-heavenspot-part-of-mc-saatchi-la/|title=Kathryn Schotthoefer Named President of Heavenspot, part of M&C Saatchi LA|author=onioneye|work=M&C Saatchi Los Angeles|accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> She is a vocal advocate for human rights and civil rights, particularly in regards to refugee humanitarian efforts. In 2016, she was awarded the Global Gift Foundation Philanthropreneur Award, an honor previously awarded to Victoria Beckham and Jorge Perez.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.shootonline.com/spw/global-gift-foundation-honor-heavenspot-president-kathryn-schotthoefer-organization%E2%80%99s-women%E2%80%99s|title=The Global Gift Foundation To Honor Heavenspot President Kathryn Schotthoefer At The Organization’s Women’s Empowerment Luncheon|work=SHOOTonline.com|accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref>  She is a native of [[Bloomfield Hills, Michigan]] and resides in [[Los Angeles, California]]. 

