The '''New Program Group''' (NPG) refers to a [[joint-venture]] [[consortium]] formed in August 1984 involving the [[Gannett Company|Gannett]], [[Hearst Television|Hearst]], [[Metromedia]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Syndication Venture Awaits word on Sale of Metromedia |author= |url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1985-05-20/business/8501200162_1_metromedia-tv-metromedia-producers-corp-npg|newspaper=Sun Sentinel |date=20 May 1985 |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref> [[Storer Communications|Storer]] and [[Taft Broadcasting|Taft]] television station<ref>{{cite news |title=FRESH FARE PUTS A NEW FACE ON INDEPENDENT STATIONS |author= |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1986/02/02/arts/fresh-fare-puts-a-new-face-on-independent-stations.html?pagewanted=2 |newspaper=New York Times |date=2 February 1986 |accessdate=4 April 2013 |first=Richard W. |last=Stevenson}}</ref> groups. The reasoning behind of the formation occurred when broadcasting companies Taft, Gannett, Hearst, and Storer, desiring to beat the rates of network production (by the early 1980s, an average network sitcom cost roughly [[United States|$]]600,000 per episode<ref>{{cite news |title=Tv Syndicators' Brave New World |author=Gendel, Morgan |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1985-03-04/entertainment/ca-24343_1_tv-syndication/2 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=4 March 1985 |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref>) and exercise more creative program control, joined forces with Metromedia Productions to produce and distribute new [[Broadcast syndication#First-run syndication in the U.S.|first-run syndicated]] TV programs. The first program from NPG was ''[[Small Wonder (TV series)|Small Wonder]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://members.surfbest.net/smallwonder@surfbest.net/SWonTV/SeriesBackground.html |title=Series Background |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |work=Small Wonder Home Page |publisher= |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tv Highlights: `Small Wonder` She`s Perfect |author=McGuire, Carolyn  |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1985-09-07/features/8502280671_1_bill-veeck-preview-vicki |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=7 September 1985 |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://radiodiscussions.com/smf/index.php?topic=105988.0;wap2 |title=Original Clearance of "Small Wonder" |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |work=RadioDiscussions.com Discussion Boards " Classic TV |publisher= |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Stations' Appetite For New Shows To Blame For Tired Small Wonder' |author= |url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1985-05-20/business/8501200162_1_metromedia-tv-metromedia-producers-corp-npg|newspaper=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |date=6 September 1985 |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= |author= |url=https://newspaperarchive.com/aiken-standard/1984-09-28/page-22 |newspaper=Aiken Standard |date=28 September 1984 |accessdate=4 April 2013}}</ref> which debuted on 7 September 1985.

