'''Pavel Vladimirovich Krasheninnikov''' ({{lang-ru|Павел Владимирович Крашенинников}}, born 21 June 1964 in [[Sverdlovsk Oblast]], [[Soviet Union]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[lawyer]] and [[politician]].

From 1998<ref>[http://www.russiajournal.com/node/619 Inside Russia's White House]</ref> to August 1999<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=nXMaAAAAIBAJ&sjid=SS8EAAAAIBAJ&pg=6515,4435921&dq=pavel-krasheninnikov+appointed&hl=en Yeltsin Again Decides To Reshuffle Russia's Cabinet Members]</ref> ([[Sergei Kiriyenko's Cabinet]], [[Yevgeny Primakov's Cabinet]], [[Sergei Stepashin's Cabinet]]) he was [[Ministry of Justice (Russia)|Justice Minister of Russia]].

[[Russian legislative election, 1999|Since 1999]] he has been a Deputy of the [[State Duma]],<ref name="Khmelnitskaya2015">{{cite book|author=Marina Khmelnitskaya|title=The Policy-Making Process and Social Learning in Russia: The Case of Housing Policy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=23WkCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT206|date=15 September 2015|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1-137-40975-1|pages=206–}}</ref> at first from [[Union of Rightist Forces]] and later joined [[United Russia]].

