{{Moroccan Royal Family}}
'''Prince Moulay Ismail of Morocco''' ({{lang-ar|إسماعيل بن مولاي عبد الله بن محمد الخامس}})
(born 7 May 1981) is the son of [[Prince Moulay Abdallah of Morocco|Prince Moulay Abdallah]] and Lalla Lamia Solh. His mother is daughter of [[Riad Al Solh]], the first [[Prime minister of Lebanon]]. The Prince has one older brother, [[Prince Moulay Hicham of Morocco|Prince Moulay Hicham]].

On 25 September 2009, he married Anissa Lehmkuhl,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.royalark.net/Morocco/morocco12.htm|title=MOROCCO12|website=www.royalark.net|access-date=2018-02-24}}</ref> the daughter of Lieutenant-Colonel Omar Lehmkuhl and his wife, Amina (German citizens converted to Islamic faith).<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |author= |coauthors= |title=SM le Roi préside à Rabat la cérémonie de conclusion de l'acte de mariage de SA le Prince Moulay Ismail |curly= |url=http://www.map.ma/fr/sections/a_la_une/sm_le_roi_preside_a/view |format= |agency= |work= |language=French |quote= |archiveurl= |archivedate= }}</ref> They had issue, one son and four daughters: 
* ''Sharif Moulay'' Abdallah, (born on {{birth date|2010|6|17|df=yes}} at Rabat),
* ''Sharifa Lalla'' Aisha, (born on {{birth date|2011|10|9|df=yes}}  at Rabat),
* ''Sharifa Lalla'' Hala, (born on {{birth date|2013|11|23|df=yes}} at Rabat).
* ''Sharifa Lalla'' Anissa, (born on {{birth date|2018|2|5|df=yes}} at Rabat).

==Business==
Prince Ismail owns Theora holding, which has a 35% stake<ref>{{cite news|title=Amine Belkhouya, gérant de Kia Maroc, le jour où tout a basculé|url=http://www.medias24.com/DROIT/11062-Amine-Belkhouya-gerant-de-Kia-Maroc-le-jour-ou-tout-a-bascule.html|accessdate=15 June 2014|date=24 April 2014}}</ref> in the now-defunct [[Kia Motors|KIA Maroc]] (exclusive dealer of KIA cars in Morocco)<ref>{{cite news|title=Kia Motors Maroc Belkhouya sous les verrous|url=http://autonews.press.ma/content/kia-motors-maroc|accessdate=15 June 2014|date=21 April 2014|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6QM1yRWS7|archivedate=15 June 2014}}</ref> and also co-owns a number of food & restaurants franchises such as [[Pizza Del Arte]] (subsidiary of [[Groupe Le Duff]]).

== Patronages ==
* Honorary President of the ''Hand in Hand'' Association.

